JOHANNESBURG – Police Minister Bheki Cele says fighting between communities and police only helps criminals. Cele said they've identified a third suspect in connection with the shooting of Sadia Sukhraj. He warned Chatsworth residents against taking vigilante action. READ: Suspect in Sadia Sukhraj murder appears in court Chatsworth community members protested outside a police station after 9-year-old Sukhraj was shot during a botched hijacking. “They benefit a lot if communities and police fight, criminals they laugh all the way. The clarion call for both the police and communities is that remember your first responsibility is to jealously guard safe your safety. Even if you find it between and among yourself not at the expense of your own safety and the safety of your kids,” Cele said. eNCA